); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Elderly abuse is an act that causes injury to an older adult, whether physical, sexual, or other. It may happen within a trusting relationship and come from those you trust.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgba(249, 248, 246, 0.48); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: left; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">Elder abuse can be challenging to detect, like other domestic or family violence types. It can happen anywhere. It usually occurs in the privacy of an older person’s house or a nursing home. Similarly, family members, friends, caregivers, or other trusted individuals are most likely the ones who do it.</p><p style="box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 1em; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; text-size-adjust: 100%; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgba(249, 248, 246, 0.48); color: rgb(102, 102, 102); font-family: Montserrat, Helvetica, Arial, Lucida, sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: nor